TITLE: UK PM Liz Truss announces another huge U-turn and names Jeremy Hunt as finance minister
SUMMARY: British Prime Minister Liz Truss on Friday scrapped another key tax-cutting policy after firing her finance minister, in a bid to placate markets after the government's controversial "mini-budget."

TITLE: JPMorgan Chase tops estimates as bank reaps more interest income than expected after jump in rates
SUMMARY: JPMorgan Chase on Friday posted results that topped analysts' estimates as the biggest U.S. bank by assets took advantage of rising rates.

TITLE: Musk says SpaceX cannot fund Starlink in Ukraine 'indefinitely' after report he asked Pentagon to pay
SUMMARY: Elon Musk has claimed that the Starlink Ukraine operation has cost SpaceX $80 million so far, and will exceed $100 million by the end of the year.

TITLE: Oil protesters arrested after throwing tomato soup at Van Gogh painting
SUMMARY: Two activists from campaign group Just Stop Oil have been arrested after throwing tomato soup on Vincent Van Gogh’s famous “Sunflowers” painting.

TITLE: U.S. satellite giant Viasat's $7.3 billion takeover of UK rival Inmarsat faces in-depth competition probe
SUMMARY: The U.K.'s competition regulator is worried the deal would lead to higher prices for onboard Wi-Fi on plane flights.

TITLE: UK's Royal Mail reveals plans to cut up to 6,000 jobs by next summer
SUMMARY: The news follows a summer of strikes by postal workers in the U.K.

TITLE: Russia looks to deprive Ukrainians of water and electricity as winter approaches
SUMMARY: Ukraine is dealing with the aftermath of another day of missile attacks with power and water supplies damaged after Russia targeted energy infrastructure.

TITLE: Sony and Honda plan to start U.S. deliveries of their electric vehicle in 2026
SUMMARY: This week's news builds on previous communications about the joint venture.

TITLE: Mark Zuckerberg said he missed a giant shift in social networking
SUMMARY: Meta CEO Mark Zuckerberg said that people are increasingly using their social networking "feeds" to discover content regardless if it was shared by friends.

TITLE: Here's the inflation breakdown for September 2022 — in one chart
SUMMARY: Inflation was hotter than expected in September. Categories such as food, energy and housing have risen sharply in the past year.

TITLE: Europe is still quietly importing Russian nuclear energy
SUMMARY: Russia's nuclear fuel industry remains conspicuously untouched by European sanctions more than seven months into the Kremlin's war in Ukraine

TITLE: China is no longer just any emerging market — it has become its own beast
SUMMARY: China is no longer just another emerging market play. The country is becoming its own beast — with all the risks and rewards that come with being a world power.

TITLE: North Korea flies warplanes near border and tests another ballistic missile
SUMMARY: Thursday's test comes less than one day after North Korea said it test-fired a long-range cruise missile.

TITLE: Xi wanted China to be at the tech frontier. 5 years on, tensions with the U.S. have dented that goal
SUMMARY: In 2017, Xi Jinping spoke about China's ambition in 'frontier' tech. Five years on, as the Communist Party's 20th National Congress approaches, results are mixed.

TITLE: White House is pushing ahead research to cool Earth by reflecting back sunlight
SUMMARY: There are several kinds of sunlight-reflection technology, and none have been thoroughly researched due to a perceived moral hazard. But sentiment is shifting.

TITLE: Singapore avoids recession as economy grows in third quarter, central bank tightens policy
SUMMARY: Singapore avoided a technical recession, with quarterly GDP growth coming in a 1.5% on a seasonally adjusted basis, after a contraction in the previous quarter.

TITLE: Globally critical chip firm tells U.S. staff to stop servicing China customers after Biden export curbs
SUMMARY: ASML, one of the world's most important semiconductor toolmakers, told U.S. employees to servicing Chinese customers in response to Washington's export curbs.

TITLE: Treasury's Yellen says Russia's war has weakened its economy 'for years to come'
SUMMARY: Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen said sanctions the U.S., the European Union and allies have levied against Russia have stunted the nation's growth prospects.

TITLE: Apple, Goldman Sachs introduce interest-bearing savings accounts as rates rise
SUMMARY: Apple continues to expand its consumer financial services offerings as it tries to broaden the ways iPhones can be used.

TITLE: Biden administration asked Saudi Arabia to postpone OPEC decision by a month, Saudis say
SUMMARY: Notably, Biden's request would have delayed the decision until after the U.S. midterm elections.

TITLE: China's consumer prices jump by the most in more than two years
SUMMARY: China's consumer prices rose in September at their fastest pace in more than two years as pork prices climbed, the National Bureau of Statistics said Friday.

TITLE: UK extends deadline to remove Huawei from 5G networks after one carrier warned of outages
SUMMARY: U.K. telcos will now have until December 2023 to remove Huawei 5G equipment from their network "cores," where some of the most sensitive data is processed.

TITLE: Tether, world's biggest stablecoin, cuts its commercial paper holdings to zero
SUMMARY: Tether has cut its commercial paper holdings to zero, replacing them with U.S. Treasury bills instead, according to a blog post.

TITLE: Netflix will charge $6.99 a month for new ad-supported plan starting Nov. 3 in U.S.
SUMMARY: Netflix is debuting its advertising-supported subscription plan on Nov. 3 in the U.S. at $6.99 per month.

TITLE: El Salvador's bitcoin experiment: $60 million lost, $375 million spent, little to show so far
SUMMARY: The use of bitcoin in El Salvador appears to be low, as the currency has lost about 60% of its value since the experiment started.

TITLE: Supreme Court denies Trump bid to void ruling in Mar-a-Lago raid documents case
SUMMARY: Donald Trump is under criminal investigation by the Department of Justice over his removal of government documents when he left the White House.

TITLE: Strikes, possible blackouts and a plunging currency: Brits are being hit by a wave of bad news
SUMMARY: The U.K. has been beset by a wave of economic and political crises in recent months.

TITLE: It wouldn't be a surprise if the ECB hikes rates above 3%, says Belgium's central bank chief
SUMMARY: "I think we are going to have to go real positive somewhere," Belgium's Pierre Wunsch told CNBC.

TITLE: Fed officials expect higher rates to stay in place, meeting minutes show
SUMMARY: The Federal Reserve released minutes Wednesday from its Sept. 20-21 meeting.

TITLE: Asian economies may have to brace for rising debt and capital flight, IMF warns
SUMMARY: Asia's biggest economic problems next year will stem from rising interest rates. These will put increasing pressure on debt servicing in Asia and heighten capital flight from the region
